item.para:
a)
Where he votes before a Registrar before polling day - he shall mark his vote on his ballot-paper in the manner prescribed by the regulations;
(b)where
his ballot-paper is a ballot-paper in accordance with Form F in the schedule - he shall place the number 1 in the square opposite the name of the candidate for whom he votes as his first preference, and shall give contingent votes for all the remaining candidates by placing the numbers 2, 3, 4 (and so on, as the case requires) in the squares opposite their names so as to indicate the order of his preference for them;
